betterquesting:10.desc:8: Pick up some rocks and sticks from the ground by right clicking, and you can also get more sticks from breaking leaves.

We are hoping you know how knapping works, (this is gonna be a long run for you if you don't) however, if you don't know how, select a stack of 2 or more rocks in your hotbar, and then right click on the ground to open the knapping interface. Recpies for knapping are in JEI.
Make sure you drop the logs and sticks in the same blockspace. Then, use the firestarter on the block below.

Timber!

Oh, and you can't actually place these like you'd expect in vanilla. They are smaller and stack like firewood. Use another material to build if you can.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Sensor, Emitter, Robot Arms and more

betterquesting:10.desc:8: Checks ember density in the chunk you are in.
Turns your molten liquids into Aspectus
Levers are needed to turn on item extractors and ember transmitters

Place on bedrock and fuel it with coal to obtain ember shards. You cant input AND output from the slot on top of the ember bore at the same time so you'll have to use a mechanical core. It allows you to interact with the ember bore through each side of the mechanical core.
This machine turns ember shards into ember. Insert ember into one of the bottom slots and you'll start to generate ember.

Place an emitter on the upper half of the Ember Activator and the receptor on the machine you want to supply with ember. To link up emitter and receptor, shift+right click the recepter with a hammer and right-click the emitter afterwards. Use a lever on the emitter to turn it on/off.
Melts ingots. Input ember and liquids from the bottom and extract from the top half of the mixer.
Most machines in this pack will require 5x5 crafting.

Let's get to work!

This process requires a hammer for flux, a barrel, and some products of flux and water, as well as logs and water. Process is well explained in JEI.

I recommend crafting the leather in bulk to reduce time for production.
